    :rtype: str\n\n    Page IDs of pages containing inlinks\n```\n\n```\n.. attribute:: inlinkAnchors\n   inlinkAnchor frequencies\n\n    :rtype: str\n\n    (Anchor text, frequency) of pages containing inlinks\n```\n\n```\n.. attribute:: wikidataQid\n\n    :rtype: str\n\n    Language and time independent Wikidata IDs (e.g. Q12345)\n```\n\n```\n.. attribute:: siteId\n\n    :rtype: str\n\n    SiteId (e.g. enwiki). The combination of WikidataQid and SiteId identifies a page in a wikipedia across time stamps. Note that PageName and PageId can change over time.\n```\n\n```\n.. attribute:: pageTags\n\n    :rtype: str\n\n    Template tags of pages, e.g. \"Good article\" or \"Vital article\"\n```\n"]}, {"name": "trec_car.read_data.PageSkeleton", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "trec_car.read_data.PageSkeleton.from_cbor", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cbor", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "trec_car.read_data.PageSkeleton.get_text", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Includes visible text of this element and below. Headings are excluded. Image Captions are included. Infoboxes are ignored. (For a version with headers and no captions see `get_text_with_headings` "]}, {"name": "trec_car.read_data.PageSkeleton.get_text_with_headings", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "include_heading", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Include all visible text below this elements. While the heading of this element is excluded, headings of subsections will be included. Captions of images are excluded."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["An abstract superclass for the various types of page elements. Subclasses include:\n\n- {class}`Section`\n- {class}`Para`\n- {class}`Image`\n"]}, {"name": "t